public EssFindAndReplaceContent.EssFindAndReplaceRowContent fetchRowContentForFindText(java.lang.String absBundleName,
                                                                                       java.lang.String transUnitKeyId,
                                                                                       java.lang.String findText)
Return RowContent only when, (1) a RowContent is available for a given absBundleName, TransUnitKeyId and (2) the given findText of that rowContent is different from the existing rowContent. If findTexts are same, the replacedText can be overwritten. If findTexts are different, it means the source/target content of same transUnit Id of same bundle gets updated concurrently. This might happen when singlular and plural findTexts refer to the same bundle and key
